  h3 The Codebase color swatches
  
  p Codebase's six color swatches are used for Codebase UI colors (for #[span.label default], #[span.label.label--primary primary], #[span.label.label--secondary secondary], #[span.label.label--success success], #[span.label.label--warning warning], and #[span.label.label--danger danger]. See #[a(href="basics.html#basics-buttons") buttons], #[a(href="basics.html#basics-badges-and-labels") badges and labels].

  p These six colors have also been used for the Codebase decoration utility classes.

  p In each color series there are 7 colors: the base color (see the middle row below) plus 3 incrementally lighter and 3 incrementally darker.
  
  p Plus, black and white have been included (without shades).

