    h4 Advanced (SCSS) users:
    
    p #[b All Codebase decoration colors are here simply to get you started]. You can override and improve them in your own website design as you make progress.
    
    p To show you how this is done, notice that there are a few extra example #[code $cb-color--*] variables and their instances in the #[code $cb-colors] SCSS map in the #[a(href="codebase/scss/00_default-variables/_default-variables.scss")  variables file], commented out. 
    
    p #[b You need to copy (a.) the whole set of color variables and (b.) the SCSS map into your styles &ndash; and then un-comment the extra colors in both]. Then during pre-processing, the class-builders in #[a(href="codebase/scss/04_decoration/_colors.scss") codebase/scss/04_decoration/_colors.scss] will generate all the decoration utility classes for colored backgrounds, borders and text.

    p By overriding the color variables and the SCSS map in this way, you have complete freedom to:
      
    ul
      li Add more color classes
      li Remove classes for colors that you never use
      li Change color class names
      li Change color values
